children.name: Launched : Feb 6, 2018 8:45 pm Elon Musk's Tesla Roadster is an electric sports car that served as the dummy payload for the February 2018 Falcon Heavy test flight and is now an artificial satellite of the Sun. Starman, a mannequin dressed in a spacesuit, occupies the driver's seat. The car and rocket are products of Tesla and SpaceX. This 2008-model Roadster was previously used by Musk for commuting, and is the only consumer car sent into space.

children.name: SpaceX's 23rd ISS resupply mission on behalf of NASA, this mission brings essential supplies to the International Space Station using the cargo variant of SpaceX's Dragon 2 spacecraft. Cargo includes several science experiments. The booster for this mission is expected to land on an ASDS. The mission will be complete with return and recovery of the Dragon capsule and down cargo.

children.name: This PWA React starter kit provided by the frontend chapter . The data on this project is provided by the public API at SpaceX-API
children.characters:
This PWA React Starter Kit  was developed and is maintained by the frontend chapter . This projects goal is to serve as a reference and to provide guidelines and best practises for future pwa react applications. 

This application offers a countdown timer for the upcoming launch, data about all the past launches and upcoming launches. Detailed data about spaceX rockets is also available. The starlink section provides coordinates and motion info about starlink satellites in orbit, updated hourly.

The source code for this project can be found at our BitBucket.
We also created dedicated documentation for our code decisions that can be found at our Confluence space

We have also conducted a UX Design Process and we have the low-fidelity prototypes available at this Basalmiq Cloud space and high-fidelity Prototypes in our figma space.

The data on this project is provided by the following public API at SpaceX-API 
The photos  used on this project are property of SpaceX and can be found on the SpaceX Flickr
This application has no affiliation with SpaceX.
